          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Tracks of positively charged particles, detected",
                "in a set of two drift chambers can be traced back",
                "through the magnetic field to the interaction point,",
                "leading to a momentum determination.  The velocities of",
                "these particles are accessible via a time-of-flight",
                "path behind the drift chambers, consisting of two",
                "scintillation hodoscopes followed by a large",
                "scintillation wall at a distance of 9.3 m, acting as a",
                "stop detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By author.  By measuring the momentum and the",
                "velocity, particles are identified via invariant mass."
              ]
            }
